-- Gamesa to Supply Toshiba With 30MW of Wind Turbines for Italy
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2012-10-02T11:25:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-02/gamesa-to-supply-toshiba-with-30mw-of-wind-turbines-for-italy.html
Gamesa Corporacion Tecnologica SA (GAM) ,
Spain’s biggest wind-turbine maker, will supply  Toshiba Corp. (6502) 
with 30 megawatts of the machines for an Italian power project.  Gamesa will supply 15 turbines of 2 megawatts each to the
site in Brindisi, Puglia, with installation starting before the
year-end, Zamudio-based Gamesa said today in a statement.  The order was signed with Genova-based Toshiba Europe T&D,
the contractor on the project developed by Eolica Erchie. Terms
weren’t disclosed. Gamesa has installed 1,506 megawatts of
turbines in Italy since entering the market in 2002, it said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
